tful.com/boise/events/famous-idaho-potato-marathon-/E0-001-004660900-2?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:45',3,0),('E0-001-029921296-7@2013041310',1,'V0-001-000489437-2','B.A.S.H','Once a Month BBP puts on a bicycle safety class for kids 14 and under. It is free to all, welcome to everyone, and a requirement for all kids receiving a bicycle. Bring your own bicycle and helmet, or if you don&#39;t have one, use ours. Participants meet at the fountain in Ann Morrison park at 10:30am. Volunteers meet at the shop at 10am.','1','','2013-04-13 10:30:00','2013-04-13 11:30:00','2010-04-14 09:42:18','2013-03-15 10:32:44','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/bash-/E0-001-029921296-7@2013041310?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:20',3,0),('E0-001-031620787-1@2013062100',1,'V0-001-001113175-8','Ride To Work Day','Mission:\nWe are a 501 c4 non-profit organization, advocating and supporting the use of motorcycles and scooters for transportation, and providing information about everyday utility riding to the public.\n \nVisit website for more information and informational materials: http://www.ridetowork.org/','1','','2013-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'2010-06-19 14:00:38','2010-06-19 14:00:41','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/ride-work-day-/E0-001-031620787-1@2013062100?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:01:25',3,0),('E0-001-033432946-9@2013040414',1,'V0-001-004503610-2','Caregiver Support Group','WHAT Caregiver Support group meeting\n\nPURPOSE For people who want support \n Mutual support \n Comfort\n Coping skills \n Friendship\n\nWHEN  Bi-Weekly starting Thursday August 26 for 12 sessions from 2 p.m. to 3:00 p.m.\n\nWHERE Nampa Hospice Office\n5700 E. Franklin Road, first floor conference room \nNampa, Idaho 83687\n\nCONTACT If you need additional information, please contact Katie Hart, BSW/ MSW Candidate at\n Cell: (208) 880-7163 \nPhone: (208) 461-1600 ex: 203\nFax: (208) 467-3635\n\n\nBeing a caregiver is hard but can be more manageable with support. Hope you can join us!','1','Free to the community','2013-04-04 14:00:00','2013-04-04 15:00:00','2010-09-02 09:29:55','2010-09-03 01:02:36','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/caregiver-support-group-/E0-001-033432946-9@2013040414?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-04 02:58:39',3,0),('E0-001-033432946-9@2013041814',1,'V0-001-004503610-2','Caregiver Support Group','WHAT Caregiver Support group meeting\n\nPURPOSE For people who want support \n Mutual support \n Comfort\n Coping skills \n Friendship\n\nWHEN  Bi-Weekly starting Thursday August 26 for 12 sessions from 2 p.m. to 3:00 p.m.\n\nWHERE Nampa Hospice Office\n5700 E. Franklin Road, first floor conference room \nNampa, Idaho 83687\n\nCONTACT If you need additional information, please contact Katie Hart, BSW/ MSW Candidate at\n Cell: (208) 880-7163 \nPhone: (208) 461-1600 ex: 203\nFax: (208) 467-3635\n\n\nBeing a caregiver is hard but can be more manageable with support. Hope you can join us!','1','Free to the community','2013-04-18 14:00:00','2013-04-18 15:00:00','2010-09-02 09:29:55','2010-09-03 01:02:36','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/caregiver-support-group-/E0-001-033432946-9@2013041814?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:36',3,0),('E0-001-033432986-7@2013040418',1,'V0-001-004503613-9','Fertility Issues Support Group','Fertility Issues Support Group\nled by\nKatie Hart, BSW/MSW Candidate\n\n\nMany share the dream of conceiving, delivering and nurturing a healthy child. Sometimes, however, pregnancy loss and infertility complicate the journey. Individuals and  couples who experience these unique life circumstances are confronted with a range of emotions including intense feelings of disillusionment, sadness, loss, fear, confusion and anger. Group participants find comfort through sharing, in a confidential setting, losses of the past, frustrations of the present and the anxieties that accompany hope for the future. Group participants will gain important coping skills and a strong support network to help with the impact this intense life experience has on interpersonal relationships, pregnancy & fertility decision-making, and dealing with the cycle of hope and hopelessness.\n\nPlease join us: First Thursday of every month starting September 2, 2010 @ 6pm. This group will be an open on-going group.\nWhere: 5700 East Franklin Road, Nampa, Idaho 83687\n* first floor conference room\nContact information:\n* Office: 208-461-1600 ex: 203\n*Cell: 208-631-4496\n*email: khart@guardianhomecare.com\n\nKatie Hart, BSW/MSW Candidate\nKatie Hart has been in the field of Social Work for over 10 years and is a Masters level Social Worker. Katie is in the process of becoming  licensed at the masters level and is currently practicing under and being supervised by LeAnn Stensgaard, LCSW.  Having personally experienced issues of pregnancy loss and infertility, she would like to provide support for individuals and couples that are dealing with fertility issues. Katie also works with individuals and couples in areas of  mental health, anxiety, depression, relationships, grief, loss, and bereavement.\n*There is no charge for this group','1','Free to the community','2013-04-04 18:00:00','2013-04-04 20:00:00','2010-09-02 09:39:01','2013-03-15 09:25:11','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/fertility-issues-support-group-/E0-001-033432986-7@2013040418?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-04 02:58:39',3,0),('E0-001-033432986-7@2013050218',1,'V0-001-004503613-9','Fertility Issues Support Group','Fertility Issues Support Group\nled by\nKatie Hart, BSW/MSW Candidate\n\n\nMany share the dream of conceiving, delivering and nurturing a healthy child. Sometimes, however, pregnancy loss and infertility complicate the journey. Individuals and  couples who experience these unique life circumstances are confronted with a range of emotions including intense feelings of disillusionment, sadness, loss, fear, confusion and anger. Group participants find comfort through sharing, in a confidential setting, losses of the past, frustrations of the present and the anxieties that accompany hope for the future. Group participants will gain important coping skills and a strong support network to help with the impact this intense life experience has on interpersonal relationships, pregnancy & fertility decision-making, and dealing with the cycle of hope and hopelessness.\n\nPlease join us: First Thursday of every month starting September 2, 2010 @ 6pm. This group will be an open on-going group.\nWhere: 5700 East Franklin Road, Nampa, Idaho 83687\n* first floor conference room\nContact information:\n* Office: 208-461-1600 ex: 203\n*Cell: 208-631-4496\n*email: khart@guardianhomecare.com\n\nKatie Hart, BSW/MSW Candidate\nKatie Hart has been in the field of Social Work for over 10 years and is a Masters level Social Worker. Katie is in the process of becoming  licensed at the masters level and is currently practicing under and being supervised by LeAnn Stensgaard, LCSW.  Having personally experienced issues of pregnancy loss and infertility, she would like to provide support for individuals and couples that are dealing with fertility issues. Katie also works with individuals and couples in areas of  mental health, anxiety, depression, relationships, grief, loss, and bereavement.\n*There is no charge for this group','1','Free to the community','2013-05-02 18:00:00','2013-05-02 20:00:00','2010-09-02 09:39:01','2013-03-15 09:25:11','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/fertility-issues-support-group-/E0-001-033432986-7@2013050218?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:23',3,0),('E0-001-033615893-5@2013041718',1,'V0-001-000623849-1','Adult Children Caring for Alzheimer\'s Parent','Are you juggling care for a parent with Alzheimer&#39;s disease. Do you simply need someone to talk to w