y simple, but the unadorned nature of his writing makes the songs all the more powerful, he has a way of cutting to the heart of a matter not unlike Kris Kristofferson. He has a unique, direct, almost lazy and often melancholic style of conveying his lyrics which lends to a very intimate feel.','','','2013-04-05 19:00:00',NULL,'2013-02-10 20:43:21','2013-02-10 20:43:21','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/lee-penn-sky-/E0-001-054474987-9?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-05 02:58:42',3,0),('E0-001-054479051-8',1,'V0-001-001605692-0','IdTA Global Cup Tournament','<p>To celebrate the international flavor of the Davis Cup (as well as the Quarterfinal match featuring the US vs. Serbia to be played in Boise April 5-7!), we hope that you&#39;ll join us at the IdTA Global Cup Tournament on Saturday, March 30 at 6 p.m. <p>The format will be a men&#39;s and women&#39;s doubles compass draw at both the 6.0 and 7.0 combo levels, with partners sharing the same home country of origin! Each match will be first to six games (no-ad scoring), with a 9-point tiebreak at 5-5. The team winning the set will advance to the next round. Every participant should expect to play at least two matches, with all matches expected to be completed by 10:30 p.m.<p>Please note that registration is single-ticket style, but it is a combo (6.0 and 7.0) event. During the registration process, please indicate your partners full name so that we can prepare the draw beforehand. Draws will be posted two days prior to the event on our website (www.idtennis.com) and our Facebook page! If you are in need of a partner, please be sure to check the &quot;Need a partner&quot; box. Awesome prizes will be awarded to the winning teams of each division so be sure to join in on the fun!<p>Court time and balls will be provided. In keeping with the international theme, players are encouraged to bring a dish from their home country to share with everyone. We have room for only 8 teams in each