k Tooth Grin - Reverend Otis & The Traveling Medicine Show','','','','2013-06-15 20:00:00',NULL,'2013-02-11 20:42:34','2013-02-11 20:42:34','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/black-tooth-grin-reverend-otis-traveling-medicine-s-/E0-001-054498728-4?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:01:16',3,0),('E0-001-054500605-4',1,'V0-001-006025568-5','Great Owyhee Ride Against Hunger 2013','<p>Billed by area riders as &quot;the one ride you should do if you only do one ride all year&quot;, The Great Owyhee Ride Against Hunger is named for a True Century Ride that starts at the Historic Ontario, OR Train Depot and winds its way up through scenic Rural Oregon, past parts of the legendary Oregon Trail, to the base of the Majestic Owyhee Dam before returning to town. Breakfast, Lunch (featuring local breweries &amp; wineries), and plenty of rest stop &amp; logistical support are provided. Proceeds from the ride benefit Oregon Food Bank-Southeast Oregon Services</p><p><strong>Directions from Freeway to Start Location</strong></p><p>From I-84</p><p>Take Exit 376A</p><p>Right on West Idaho Ave (towards City Center)</p><p>Left on South Oregon (after the Underpass) </p><p>Towards Downtown</p><p>Left on SE 3rd Avenue (landmarks include area businesses Alvarado Jewelers, Eastside Florist, The Competition and Jolts and Juice Coffee Company)</p><p>Proceed to Historic Ontario Train Depot (should be lots of parking). Event Signage, Registration Tables, &amp; Continental Breakfast area should be visible once parked.</p><p><strong>From Hwy 20/26 (coming from Vale)</strong></p><p>Left @ Light (junction Hwy 20/26 &amp; Hwy 55)</p><p>Towards Ontario</p><p>Right @ SW 4th Avenue</p><p>SW 4th Avenue to SW Oregon St (Downtown Ontario)</p><p>Right @ SE 3rd Avenue</p><p>Proceed to Historic Ontario Train Depot</p>','','','2013-06-15 00:00:00','2013-06-15 00:00:00','2013-02-11 21:47:25','2013-03-24 08:52:55','evdb','http://eventful.com/ontario_or/events/great-owyhee-ride-against-hunger-2013-/E0-001-054500605-4?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:01:15',3,0),('E0-001-054501238-3',1,'V0-001-000839550-5','Cycle for Independence 2013','<p>Treasure Valley Chapter, National Federation of the Blind of Idaho (NFBI) brings hope and confidence to blind people. Adjusting to blindness is not fun, but with proper help newly blinded people can learn to lead active and satisfying lives.</p><p> </p><p>The NFB ...</p><p>Awards scholarships to blind college students</p><p>Publishes Braille and recorded materials about blindness</p><p>Provides information about blindness to sighted people</p><p>Advocates for blind people who face discrimination</p><p>Assists blind people in finding employment</p><p>Develops new technology for the blind</p><p>Makes newspapers and magazines available to the blind by telephone (NFB-Newsline)</p><p>You are helping change what it means to be blind. Although there is a lot of work left to do, the world is truly a better place for the blind today. Thank you.</p><p>For more information about blindness or to arrange a speaking engagement for a class or organization, call: (208) 336-5333 or write: </p><p>Treasure Valley Chapter, National Federation of the Blind of Idaho, PO Box 2007, Boise, ID 83701</p><p>Riders who pre-registration receive:</p><p>Free bike socks!</p><p>Team recognition for groups of 5 or more.</p><p>Fee reduction of $5 for team riders until May 11. Pre-registration ends May 14.</p><p>All Riders Receive:</p><p>Riders and volunteers will receive a goody bag, free lunch, and an opportunity to win exciting door prizes!! </p><p>Get a Team Together!</p><p>A team is five riders or more. Pick a Team Captain and sign up with family members, neighbors, or co-workers. Dress your team in t-shirts or company apparel so we can recognize your group. Challenge other teams to meet or beat the number of riders in your group. Team riders receive a $5 discount until May 11. After this you may pre-register until May 14 without the discount. We encourage riders the day of the ride as well.</p><p>Blind Driver Challenge</p><p>The first public demonstration of a blind man driving a car occurred January 29, 2011 preceding the Rolex 24 Daytona. The NFB is leading the way toward better integration and opportunities for the blind. Go to www.nfb.org/nfb-blind-driver-challenge for more information.</p>','','','2013-05-18 00:00:00','2013-05-18 00:00:00','2013-02-11 22:10:03','2013-03-24 08:57:15','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/cycle-independence-2013-/E0-001-054501238-3?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:45',3,0),('E0-001-054507898-1',1,'V0-001-001699065-1','2013 Chair Affair Lecture Series','2013 Lecture Series; Past  / Present / Future of Design April 19th / Lecture Series // 10:30am-2:30pm - WaterCooler at 1405 West Idaho Street$20 General / $15 Students, Includes lectures and lunch provided by Saint Lawrence Gridiron.10:30am-11:30am Past:  Amy Pence Brown of Idaho Modern 11:45am-1:15pm Present: Jordan Cappella, Designer (HGTV)1:30pm-2:30pm Future: Designers Panel featuring Amy Pence Brown, Jordan Cappella, and Dwaine Carver  General Admission - $20.00 Student (w/ ID) - $15.00','','$15.00 - $20.00','2013-04-19 10:30:00',NULL,'2013-02-12 03:48:00','2013-02-12 03:48:00','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/2013-chair-affair-lecture-series-/E0-001-054507898-1?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:37',3,0),('E0-001-054507941-2',1,'V0-001-006651959-4','2013 Chair Affair Competition Entry Fee','Complete rules please visit: bit.ly/QxaDpFFill out an Online Form: bit.ly/O5Diy6   Please mark on your entry form that you have paid online. Entry forms must be emailed no later than April 12th, 2013, to Kimberly Crystal-Allen at kimberlyc@pacmat.com. Entries must be assembled or manufactured between April 21, 2012 and April 19, 2013. Entries are to be delivered to the Gala site the day before the event (Fr