d in 1955, also the year of the &quot;Boys of Boise&quot; sex scandal that brought Boise to national attention as an anti-homosexuality frenzy gripped the city, and destroyed lives and reputations. Mark will delve into the connection between what happened in Boise in 1955, what was happening nationally at that time, and take a look at these issues in 2013; (with musical selections from the opera.)</p>','','','2013-04-18 00:00:00','2013-04-18 00:00:00','2013-02-16 19:10:03','2013-02-16 19:10:03','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/susannah-mccarthyism-and-boys-boise-/E0-001-054605667-6?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:36',3,0),('E0-001-054605675-5',1,'V0-001-000179424-8','BOISE\'S HISTORIC STREETSCAPES','BOISE&#39;S HISTORIC STREETSCAPES <br> 04.25.2013 <br> 6:30-8:00 PM <br> Sesqui-Shop (1008 Main St.) <br> <a href=\"http://www.boise150.org/projects/city/sesqui-speaks/streetscapes/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.boise150.org/projects/city/sesqui-speaks/streetscapes/</a><p> Boise&#39;s 150 year history is revealed by a look at its historic streetscapes. Using maps, historic images, and plats Historian Barbara Perry Bauer will trace city history in a presentation that discusses Grove Street (orginally called Market Street, one of Boise&#39;s first streets. Warm Springs Avenue and Harrison Boulevard reflect changing trends in architecture and city development during the 1890s and 1900s. Post war development is revealed with a look at Bench streets including Vista Avenue and Crescent Rim Drive. Randolph and Robertson streets reflect mid-century architectural changes and Bown Way captures today&#39;s modern development and architecture.</p>','','','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-02-16 19:10:29','2013-02-24 17:24:22','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/boises-historic-streetscapes-/E0-001-054605675-5?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:53',3,0),('E0-001-054605678-2',1,'V0-001-0