882-5?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-03-29 15:00:23',3,0),('E0-001-054943811-8@2013033119',1,'V0-001-000105395-6','Tea Meditation','Event is located at 2726 W Smith Ave. Boise. \nCome join us for one hour of relaxation with tea, Qigong breathing exercise, and guided meditation.','','$5 per class','2013-03-31 19:00:00','2013-03-31 20:00:00','2013-03-04 09:53:23','2013-03-04 09:53:23','evdb','http://eventful.com/nampa/events/tea-meditation-/E0-001-054943811-8@2013033119?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-03-29 15:00:23',3,0),('E0-001-054947547-4',1,'V0-001-002986667-3','NW Energy Coalition\'s Spring 2013 NW Clean & Affordable Energy Conference','<p>Please join us this spring at the NW Energy Coalition’s NW Clean & Affordable Energy Conference in Boise, Idaho May 31 – June 1 where experts from Idaho and across the Northwest will address some of the region’s most exciting energy issues.<p><strong>Conference agenda highlights:</strong><strong> </strong><ul><li><strong>Panel: The power of small-scale renewables: Opportunities in the Northwest</strong></li></ul><p>The region is increasing it reliance on small-scale renewables. Panelists will examine the policies that are moving Idaho and other Northwest states toward distributed generation resources such as solar and wind power, including feed-in tariffs, net-metering and consumer incentive programs.<ul><li><strong>Panel: From urban to rural: Harvesting more energy efficiency</strong></li></ul><p>Energy efficiency is our most abundant clean energy resource, but how can we secure all the energy efficiency we need? The panel will explore the challenges of acquiring energy efficiency in rural and urban communities, such as population density, delivery costs, condition of low-income housing stocks, and look at agricultural energy-saving opportunities.<ul><li><strong>Panel: A bend in the river: A stakeholder process for Columbia-Snake salmon recovery and the Army Corps’ sediment dilemma</strong></li></ul><p>A new opportunity has arisen to craft a comprehensive solution to restoring endangered Columbia Basin salmon. Panelists will discuss the opportunities presented by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Fisheries stakeholder process and bring us up-to-date on the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers’ study on sediment management needs on the Snake River.<ul><li>F<strong>riday evening reception and awards presentation</strong></li></ul><ul><li><strong>And don’t miss Saturday’s clean energy tour in downtown Boise!</strong></li></ul><p> <p><a href=\"http://www.nwenergy.org/conference\" rel=\"nofollow\">Click here for a full agenda and additional information on lodging, location and conference speakers.</a><br></p></p></p></p></p></p></p>','','','2013-05-31 08:00:00','2013-06-01 13:00:00','2013-03-04 13:34:54','2013-03-30 12:21:35','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/nw-energy-coalitions-spring-2013-nw-clean-affordable-/E0-001-054947547-4?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:01:01',3,0),('E0-001-054950575-7',1,'V0-001-001502712-5','Gymnastics Summer Registration','We offer classes for boys and girls ages walking- 1 to 4, 5 and up, Competitive Team, Mommy/Daddy and Me classes. -all classes open enrollment \nOur classes think of the whole child. The benefits of gymnastics help build muscle strength, cardiovascular endurance, flexibility, balance, coordination, agility, socialization skills, learn how to set goals, and gain an awareness for leading a healthy lifestyle.','','','2013-05-06 08:00:00','2013-05-06 20:30:00','2013-03-04 15:45:14','2013-03-04 15:45:14','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/gymnastics-summer-registration-/E0-001-054950575-7?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:28',3,0),('E0-001-054950595-1@2013040610',1,'V0-001-001502712-5','Family Wall Crawl','We have up to 25 top-rope sections, numerous bouldering challenges, a rope ladder, and our huge &