52',3,0),('E0-001-055214349-6',1,'V0-001-006722007-7','Idaho Financial Literacy Month Proclamation Signing 2013','<p>Dear Members and Friends of the Idaho Financial Literacy Coalition,<p>You are hereby invited to join us at Governor Otter&#39;s ceremonial office for the signing of the April 2013 Financial Literacy Month Proclamation Ceremony and Recognition of Piggy Bank Beauty Contest Winners. Please RSVP by clicking on the &quot;Attend Event&quot; button.<p>Lt. Governor Brad Little will be the state official present for the ceremony.<p><strong>When</strong>: Wednesday, April 3, 2013 from 12:00-12:30 pm<p><strong>Where</strong>: Governor Otter&#39;s Ceremonial Office, Idaho State Capitol, 2nd Floor West Wing (there is a small possibility that the Lt Governor may need to change the location, but attendees will be notified if that is the case)<p><strong>Who</strong>: Winners of Idaho&#39;s 3rd Annual Piggy Bank Beauty Contest and their family and guests, Members and Guests of the Idaho Financial Literacy Coalition, Representatives of Get $mart Idaho, and others with an interest in promoting a more financial capable population in Idaho.<p><strong>Parking</strong>: Street-side metered and unmetered parking, the Visitors Parking Lot at State Street and 4th Street (near the Idaho Commission for Libraries building), and the Visitors Parking Lot at 6th Street and Washington Street (behind the Len B. Jordan building)<p><strong>What to Expect</strong>: Lieutenant Governor Brad Little will read Governor Otter&#39;s proclamation stating that April is Financial Literacy Month in Idaho. He will also recognize the winners of the Coalition&#39;s Piggy Bank Beauty Contest, and there will be an opportunity for the winners and their parents to take a picture with the Lt Governor. We also hope to have a group photo take with Lt Governor Little.<p><strong>What to Do</strong>: Please pass this invitation to anyone you think might be interested in or should be involved in the promotion of financial literacy in Idaho. If you have any contacts with the media, please invite them as well.<p><strong>Questions?</strong> Please contact Coalition President Todd Christensen at <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/xml/event_search?app_key=NTgyMmViMzU3Y2Rj&user_key=12754381904766637140&max=100&page=972&tracking_link=eventful_item_97069\" rel=\"nofollow\">Education@DebtReductionServices.org</a> or 208-378-0200 x 906.<p>Space is limited, so please RSVP as soon as possible.<p>Thank you for your support of financial education in Idaho. I look forward to seeing you soon.<p>Todd <p><a></a><strong>Todd Christensen<br></strong>Director of Education<p> <p><strong><em>&quot;One Team, One Focus&quot;</em></strong><p>National Financial Education Center<br>at Debt Reduction Services Inc<p>6213 N Cloverdale Rd Ste 100<br>Boise ID 83713<br>(208) 378-0200 x 906<br>(208) 685-1058 Fax<br><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/xml/event_search?app_key=NTgyMmViMzU3Y2Rj&user_key=12754381904766637140&max=100&page=972&tracking_link=eventful_item_97069\" rel=\"nofollow\">TChristensen@DebtReductionServices.org</a><br><a href=\"http://www.debtreductionservices.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.DebtReductionServices.org</a></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p>','','Coalition Members  0.00 <br><br>   Contest Winners  0.00 <br><br>','2013-04-03 12:00:00','2013-04-03 12:30:00','2013-03-15 08:06:51','2013-03-30 17:22:29','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/idaho-financial-literacy-month-proclamation-signing-2-/E0-001-055214349-6?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-03 02:58:46',3,0),('E0-001-055215597-8',1,'V0-001-006811965-3','The Art of Marriage','<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xEEWvJ8XrLg&feature=player_embedded\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xEEWvJ8XrLg&feature=player_embedded</a><p> Impacting you. So you can impact others.<p>The Art of Marriage Event is a video experience designed for church and community settings.  The Art of Marriage Event consists of six video sessions typically held on a Friday night and Saturday.  These videos combine dramatic stories, real-life testimonies, expert interviews, humorous vignettes and other teaching methods to lay out God’s design for marriage in a fresh, engaging way.  Guests attending the event are each provided a manual with projects to help them apply the principles taught in each session, augmented by dozens of articles and additional content to help them dive deeper.<p>Since our launch in 2011, over 260,000 people have been impacted by The Art of Marriage, and MANY have dedicated their lives to Christ for the first time!</p></p></p></p>','','NCF The Art of Marriage 22.09 <br><br>','2013-04-26 19:00:00','2013-04-27 09:00:00','2013-03-15 09:42:31','2013-03-15 09:42:31','evdb','http://eventful.com/nyssa/events/art-marriage-/E0-001-055215597-8?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:04',3,0),('E0-001-055216196-0',1,'V0-001-001070291-1','Spring Garden Class - What\'s New?','<p><strong>What&#39;s New in flower varieties this year. Garnette Edwards (3rd generation owner) will share the newest trends for the year. Weather permitting, we will hold the class outside in our beautiful Legacy Garden Gazebo.</strong><p> </p></p>','','What&#39;s New? 0.00 <br><br>','2013-04-06 10:30:00','2013-04-06 11:45:00','2013-03-15 10:29:49','2013-03-15 10:29:49','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/spring-garden-class-whats-new-/E0-001-055216196-0?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-06 02:58:23',3,0),('E0-001-055216235-8',1,'V0-001-001070291-1','Spring Garden Class - Creating a Garden Tapestry','<p>Mary Ann Newcomer will present &quot;Creating Beautiful Garden Tapestries&quot;. Finding the common but colorful threads that weave a garden together. Some folks instinctively know “what goes with what”. The rest of us struggle to find perfect perennial partners for the garden. How DO you create pleasing, colorful, compositions in your beds and borders? Garden designers know to look for the common color characteristics, or color “echoes,” and tie them together from one plant to the next for a harmonious composition. This program will showcase gorgeous color combinations you can make work at home. Mary Ann Newcomer, scribe-scout-speaker has her own blog, to check it out click here. She’s known as the Dirt Diva on the River Radio, 94.9 in Boise, ID. Her articles on gardening have been published in MaryJane’s Farm, Fine Gardening, and American Gardener. An accomplished horticulturalist, and garden designer, she has wielded her creativity and design talents on public, private and commercial gardens and landscapes. Her first book, The Rocky Mountain Gardener’s Guide is in stores now. She will have this book on hand and will sign copies for those who wish. Weather permitting, we will be holding the class outside in our beautiful Legacy Garden Gazebo.<p> <p> </p></p></p>','','Creating a Garden Tapestry 0.00 <br><br>','2013-04-13 10:30:00','2013-04-13 11:45:00','2013-03-15 10:33:03','2013-03-15 10:33:03','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/spring-garden-class-creating-garden-tapestry-/E0-001-055216235-8?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:21',3,0),('E0-001-055216253-4',1,'V0-001-001070291-1','Spring Garden Class - Drought Tolerant','<p>: Dale Donahue of Desert Design will talk about plants for our dry conditions. Dale is a desert plant expert and knows our area and all of its diverse conditions. You will be amazed at how beautiful your garden can be when planted with drought tolerant and desert landscaping. Native and drought tolerant plants also attract and benefit the birds, animals and insects of our area. Weather permitting, we will be holding the class outside in our beautiful Legacy Garden Gazebo.<p> </p></p>','','Drought Tolerant Plants 0.00 <br><br>','2013-04-20 10:30:00','2013-04-20 11:45:00','2013-03-15 10:34:36'