ned to teach the fundamentals and rules of tennis in a fun, family-friendly, and interactive group environment. Ages five and above are welcome and encouraged. Bringing your own tennis racquet is recommended, although some will be available at the courts.</p>','','Visit EventBrite.com for pricing.','2013-05-11 09:00:00','2013-06-01 10:30:00','2013-04-04 12:12:13','2013-04-04 12:12:13','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/tennis-101-fort-boise-community-center-may-2013-/E0-001-055807160-5?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 03:00:39',3,0),('E0-001-055808245-2',1,'V0-001-002249834-9','Treasure the Valley April 18 Valley-Wide Lunch Meeting','<p><strong>A MESSAGE FROM YOUR HOST</strong><p><strong>TREASURE THE VALLEY LEADERSHIP TEAM</strong><p><strong> </strong><p><strong>Transforming Neighborhood Schools Summit</strong><p>Besides the local church, where do families gather in large numbers for specific purposes?  The neighborhood school!  In the USA our schools have grown in visibility and influence over the last century but has the Body of Christ responded to the needs and helped provide guidance to our local schools or have we abandoned them?<p> <p>Come explore the role of Christians and the local church in today&#39;s public schools.  State and local public school experts and school-based ministry leaders will address this issue and provide guidance and insight.  If you believe like we do that the local school is a place upon which we can actively demonstrate the love of God, then you should plan on attending.<p> <p><strong>DATE</strong>:  Thursday, April 18, 2013<p><strong>TIME</strong>:  11 AM - 1 PM (check in begins at 10:45 AM)<p><strong>LOCATION</strong>:  Vineyard Boise, 4950 Bradley Ave., Garden City<p><strong>LUNCH</strong> will be provided for those who register<p>by 11 AM on Wednesday, April 17. <p><strong>COST</strong>:  No Charge. We will receive donations to cover lunch costs from<p>those who would like to help.<p> <p><stron