tate.edu</a>.</p>','','','2013-04-19 00:00:00','2013-04-19 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:33:05','2013-04-08 13:33:05','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/april-19-student-union-performance-series-last-king-o-/E0-001-056017804-4?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:37',3,0),('E0-001-056017812-3',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','April 20-21: Seven Arrows Powwow','<p>Grand entries at Noon and 7 p.m. April 20; 7 p.m. April 21. Student Union Jordan Ballroom. Pow wow means high-energy entertainment in colorful regalia, a vibrant culture featuring song and dance, traditional craft vendors, storytelling and demonstrations. $5 general, $3 children 6-12, free for Boise State students with ID, seniors and children under 6. Call 426-5950.<p>Powwow means high-energy entertainment in colorful regalia, a vibrant culture featuring song and dance, traditional craft vendors, storytelling and demonstrations.<p> </p></p></p>','','','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-21 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:33:29','2013-04-08 13:33:29','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/april-2021-seven-arrows-powwow-/E0-001-056017812-3?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:41',3,0),('E0-001-056017850-3',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','April 20: Rodney Atkins','<p>7:30 p.m. Taco Bell Arena. Rodney Atkins comes to Boise with his “Most Hits for the Money” tour featuring Josh Thompson. Atkins knows the value of taking the long way home, of veering off the beaten path onto that road less traveled. You can hear it in his music, in the lyrics of his smash single, “Take a Back Road,” a song that celebrates that feeling of getting away from the noise of everyday life, really living in the moment and getting right with your soul. Tickets are $25-$35 at <a href=\"http://idahotickets.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">idahotickets.com</a>.</p>','','','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:34:26','2013-04-08 13:34:26','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/april-20-rodney-atkins-/E0-001-056017850-3?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:40',3,0),('E0-001-056017863-7',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','April 20: Senior Recital, Emily O’Connor, soprano','<p>3:30 p.m. Morrison Center Recital Hall. Free. Call 426-1596</p>','','','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:34:46','2013-04-08 13:34:46','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/april-20-senior-recital-emily-oconnor-soprano-/E0-001-056017863-7?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:41',3,0),('E0-001-056018050-8',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','Executive MBA Open House','<p>5:30-7:30 p.m. Thursday, April 25. Stueckle Sky Center, The Loft, 5th Floor. Boise State University has scheduled Executive MBA (EMBA) informational open houses for individuals and companies to learn more about this unique program. Free parking is provided in the general parking area of the stadium just outside the entrance to the Sky Center. Beverages and hors d’oeuvres will be served. Email <a href=\"mailto:emba@boisestate.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">emba@boisestate.edu</a> or call 426-4034 to make a reservation.</p>','','','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:38:37','2013-04-08 13:38:37','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/executive-mba-open-house-/E0-001-056018050-8?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:53',3,0),('E0-001-056018355-0',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','Service Saturday','<p>9 a.m. – 2 p.m. Apr. 20 “Service Saturday”<p>Get your volunteer on!<p>Service Saturday is a direct Service opportunity for all members of the Boise State community. This is Boise State’s way of providing easily accessible volunteer opportunities to the university community with the help of charitable and non-profit agencies.<p>Service Saturday is a great way for students, faculty, staff, alumni, and community members to collectively give back to the community in a concentrated manner. It also allows the university community to serve as active citizens in their local communities.<p>In addition to serving the community, volunteers also learn about community issues tied with the agency through reflective exercises facilitated by student Site Leaders. Our hope is that through a greater awareness of community issues, volunteers will continue to volunteer and also take action to confront these issues.<p><strong>Breakfast will be provided so come hungry!</strong><p>Saturday, April 20<br> 9am-2pm<br> Barnwell Room, SUB<p><strong>RSVP for Service Saturday <a href=\"http://orgsync.com/23254/forms/54971\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a></strong><p>For more information visit our <a href=\"http://involvement.boisestate.edu/content/article.cfm?article_id=94\" rel=\"nofollow\">Service Saturday.</a><p>Are you interested in becoming a site leader? Fill out the form <a href=\"http://orgsync.com/23254/forms/50405\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.<p>Get (IN)volved.<br><a href=\"http://getinvolved.boisestate.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">getinvolved.boisestate.edu</a></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p></p>','','','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-20 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:44:03','2013-04-08 13:44:03','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/service-saturday-/E0-001-056018355-0?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:41',3,0),('E0-001-056018367-5',1,'V0-001-000323937-4','Thursday Blockbuster Series: Django Unchained','<p>7 p.m. Apr. 25<p>Join us for Thursday Blockbuster Series with a showing of <strong>Django Unchained</strong>, written and directed by Quentin Tarantino, starring Jamie Foxx and Leonardo DiCaprio. Bring your friends and enjoy some free popcorn and soda.<p><strong>Free for students, $1.00 for non-students</strong>.<br> Click<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eUdM9vrCbow\" rel=\"nofollow\"> here</a> to view the movie trailer.<br> Get (IN)volved.<br><a href=\"http://getinvolved.boisestate.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">getinvolved.boisestate.edu</a></p></p></p>','','','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-04-25 00:00:00','2013-04-08 13:44:17','2013-04-08 13:44:17','evdb','http://eventful.com/boise/events/thursday-blockbuster-series-django-unchained-/E0-001-056018367-5?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic','2013-04-10 02:59:54',3,0);
INSERT INTO `data_events` VALUES ('E0-001-056031915-5',1,'V0-001-006891758-7','Boise State Public Radio and StoryCorps Community Partnership Meeting','<p> <p><p> <p> <p> <p>We&#39;re pleased to invite you to partner with <a href=\"http://www.storycorps.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>StoryCorps</strong></a>, one of the largest oral history projects in the U.S.! We travel the country year-round recording the stories, life experiences and conversations of everyday people. Each conversation is recorded on a free CD to share, and is preserved at the American Folk Life Center at the <strong><a href=\"http://www.loc.gov/folklife/storycorpsfaq.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Library of Congress</a></strong>. Selected stories are broadcast every Friday on NPR&#39;s <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/series/4516989/storycorps\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em><strong>Morning Edition</strong></em></a>. Local stories will also be broadcast on <strong><a href=\"http://www.boisestatepublicradio.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Boise State Public Radio</a>.</strong><p>            <p><strong>What people are saying...</strong><ul><li><em>&quot;Wonderful, wish we had more time! The atmosphere was very conducive to talking; we felt very comfortable there.&quot;</em><li><em>&quot;</em><em><strong>I must say - from the moment we reserved our time, we were treated with great care and professionalism. You do great work! Blessings to all!</strong>&quot;</em><li><em>&quot;This was a memorable experience and treasured time spent with my lifelong friend.&quot;</em><li>&quot;<em><strong>The experience touched us both very deeply.&quot;</strong></em></li></li></li></li></ul><em><br></em><strong>Listen to stories:</strong><ul><li><em><strong><a href=\"http://storycorps.org/listen/paul-crowley-and-anthony-bravo-esparza/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Paul Crowley with his barber Anthony Bravo Esparza: &quot;I&#39;ve never seen you turn anybody away.&quot;</a></strong></em><li><a href=\"http://storycorps.org/listen/bishop-ricardo-ramirez/\" 